  "title": "Warehouse Assistant (E-commerce|East|$14/hr)",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></u></p><ul><li><strong>Order Fulfillment:</strong> Picking and packing customer orders quickly and accurately.</li><li><strong>Warehouse Management:</strong> Opening/closing procedures, organizing goods in racks, chillers, and freezers.</li><li><strong>Inbound Logistics:</strong> Receiving deliveries from suppliers.</li><li><strong>Delivery Coordination:</strong> Scheduling and working with driver partners.</li><li><strong>Inventory Control:</strong> Monitoring stock aging, expiries, and temperature logs.</li><li><strong>Safety & Cleanliness:</strong> Maintaining a safe and clean environment.</li><li><strong>Cross-functional Collaboration:</strong> Working with other teams for smooth operations.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Work schedule</strong></u></p><ul><li>44 hours a week</li><li>Six 6-8 hour shifts a week</li><li>Rotating shifts between 6am and 12am</li><li>Transport to/from claimable if no public transport available </li></ul><p><u> </u><u><strong>Essential Experience / Criteria</strong></u></p><ul><li><strong>Technical Skills:</strong> Familiarity with IMS/WMS systems, barcode scanning, and basic reporting tools (Excel/Google Sheets).</li><li><strong>Soft Skills:</strong> Strong communication, organizational ability, and responsibility.</li><li><strong>Work Conditions:</strong> Ability to handle fast-paced, high-pressure environments and commit to rotating shifts (including weekends/public holidays).</li><li><strong>Preferred Background:</strong> Experience in supermarket, e-commerce, or supply chain operations.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Next Step</strong></u></p><ul><li>Drop your resume and contact us to follow-up, or send your resume to <u><strong>isaac.tanye@adecco.com</strong></u></li><li>Email Topic: Picker Packer (E-commerce|East|2.4k)</li><li>Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted</li></ul><p>Isaac Tan Yang En EA</p><p>Licence No: 91C2918</p><p>Personnel Registration No: R24123927</p>",
